'''衣夾'''，又稱'''洗衣夹'''、'''晾衣夾'''、'''曬衣夾'''，是一种能把[[衣服|衣服]]、[[被子|被子]]之类的东西夹在固定物体上以便烘干、[[晾曬|晾曬]]]的[[紧固件|紧固件]]，常见的材质是[[木材|木材]]、[[塑料|塑料]]、[[金属|金属]]等。

在洗衣夹出现之前，人们一般将衣服晾在[[灌木丛|灌木丛]]、[[树枝|树枝]]一类的地方，或晾在[[衣架|衣架]]、[[衣裳竹|衣裳竹]]上。1809年，杰里米·维克多·奥普德贝克（{{lang-en|Jérémie Victor Opdebec}}，出身不明，从名字推定，他可能是[[比利时|比利时]]人）发明了一种不带弹簧的衣夹，是为现代衣夹的鼻祖<ref>{{cite news |title=The curious history of the clothespeg |url=https://medium.economist.com/the-curious-history-of-the-clothespeg-3f8615519c61 |accessdate=21 August 2020 |work=Medium |publisher=The Economist |date=22 December 2016 |language=en}}</ref>。1853年大卫·M.史密斯发明了第一款带弹簧的衣夹，并为这种设计申请了美国[[专利|专利]]。这种带弹簧的衣夹已与现代的衣夹相当接近<ref name=who>{{cite news |first1=Hilary |last1=Greenbaum |last2=Charles Wilson |title=Who Made That Clothespin? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/05/13/magazine/who-made-that-clothespin.html |quote=The first design that resembles the modern clothespin was patented in 1853 by David M. Smith, a prolific Vermont inventor. |newspaper=The New York Times Magazine |date=May 11, 2012 |accessdate=May 11, 2012 |archive-date=2021-01-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125234345/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/05/13/magazine/who-made-that-clothespin.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |first=Anita |last=Lahey |date=Fall 2006 |title=The Better Clothespin |url=http://www.americanheritage.com/articles/magazine/it/2006/2/2006_2_38.shtml |journal=American Heritage of Invention & Technology |volume=22 |issue=2 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100119080606/http://www.americanheritage.com/articles/magazine/it/2006/2/2006_2_38.shtml |archivedate=2010-01-19 |access-date=August 11, 2015 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>
